NAME

      gcloud preview deployment-manager deployments create - insert (Create) a
         deployment using a specified template

SYNOPSIS

      gcloud preview deployment-manager deployments create DEPLOYMENT
         [--api-version API_VERSION; default="v1beta2"]
         [--description DESCRIPTION] [--format FORMAT] [--help]
         [--no-poll-for-completion] [--overrides [OVERRIDES ...]]
         [--polling-period POLLING_PERIOD; default="10"] [--project PROJECT]
         [--quiet, -q] --template TEMPLATE [-h]

DESCRIPTION

      Insert (Create) a deployment using a specified template.

POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS

      DEPLOYMENT

         Deployment name.

FLAGS

      --description DESCRIPTION

         Deployment description.

      --no-poll-for-completion

         Do not poll continuously for deployment completion. If set, only one
         Get API call is made. (default=False)

      --overrides [OVERRIDES ...]

         Optional "Path=Value Path=Value ..." template overrides. Overrides must
         be a list of space delimited key=value pairs. This overrides existing
         template settings for this deployment but does not change the template
         itself. Example: --overrides
         $.modules.foo.replicaPoolModule.numReplicas=20
         $.modules.bar.replicaPoolModule.numReplicas=5 ...

      --polling-period POLLING_PERIOD; default="10"

         Number of seconds to sleep between consecutive polls. Only effective
         when --poll-for-completion is provided.

      --template TEMPLATE

         Name of the template to use. The template must exist in the system
         before creating the deployment.

GLOBAL FLAGS

      --api-version API_VERSION; default="v1beta2"

         Optional API version.

      --format FORMAT

         Specify a format for printed output. By default, a command-specific
         human-friendly output format is used. Setting this flag to one of the
         available options will serialize the result of the command in the
         chosen format and print it to stdout. Supported formats are: json,
         text, yaml.

      --help

         Display detailed help.

      --project PROJECT

         The Google Cloud Platform project name to use for this invocation. If
         omitted then the current project is assumed.

      --quiet, -q

         Disable all interactive prompts when running gcloud commands. If input
         is required, defaults will be used, or an error will be raised.

      -h

         Print a summary help and exit.

NOTES

      This command is in the Google Cloud SDK preview component. See installing
      components if it is not installed.

